## Context

- **DB was reset since last run.** Re-registered project as 'analysis' status. Created journal entry and tasks for research_director and developer.
- **Phase 2 longitudinal validation complete on MIMIC-IV demo v2.2.** 100 patients, 275 admissions, 245 labeled. Sepsis-3 labeling: 113 sepsis (46.1%). XGBoost 5-fold CV: AUROC=0.833, AUPRC=0.835.
- **FP signature (Phase 1 replication):** At 90% spec (14 FPs): older age (d=+0.89, p<0.001), elevated BUN (d=+0.89, p=0.025), low hemoglobin (d=-0.54, p=0.039), low PaO2 (d=-0.79, p=0.023). Pattern: subclinical renal impairment + anemia = known sepsis risk factors.
- **Longitudinal tracking (Phase 2 core):** IRR=1.35 at 80% spec (FP 59.3% vs TN 43.8%, Fisher p=0.195, OR=1.87). Trend in expected direction but not significant. High baseline sepsis rate (46%) creates ceiling effect. Severely underpowered (n=27 FPs).
- **Interpretation:** FP phenotype is clinically coherent (pre-morbid risk), not random noise. Demo dataset too small for definitive test. Full MIMIC-IV (>40k patients) would provide adequate power.
- **Outputs:** data/results/false-positive-biomarker-mining/phase2/ (12 files: model_results.json, profiles, longitudinal tracking, report).
- **Script:** scripts/run_fp_mimic_longitudinal.py — end-to-end Phase 2 pipeline.
- **Previous Phase 1 outputs (CRC, COMPOSER temporal) were lost in DB reset.** CRC raw data still in data/diagnostics/crc-liquid-biopsy-panel/. COMPOSER demo data still in data/diagnostics/false-positive-biomarker-mining/composer_demo/.
- **Next:** (1) Full MIMIC-IV dataset for definitive longitudinal test (developer task created). (2) Temporal model instead of cross-sectional. (3) Cross-domain FP comparison (CRC vs sepsis). (4) FP sub-phenotype clustering.
